[thinking] I'm considering how to implement methods while avoiding deprecated APIs. It's important because we might have to deal with an interface that uses deprecated interface methods. I wonder if using a DefaultResourceManager with private constructor for injection would work. While I could consider mocks, they might not fit well. It's interesting that we might avoid using FileLocator for FormatterFactory but need it for FormatterStep.
