ng PlexusResource and see what exceptions come up. \\n\\nIn Gradle, it’s interesting how runtime dependencies for testImplementation might behave differently from compile dependencies. Also, it appears tests can't import FileLocator, which is in the plugin. I wonder if the ResourceManager class will require plexus-resources on the compile classpath due to plugin metadata. Checking module metadata will help clarify things!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_9rPQqT80taraa3cunhjE8EM2|fc_0ab6c4ff17837145016a2860166a208190b7d19e68dd51e720", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "python3 - <<'PY'\nimport urllib.request\nurl='https://repo1.maven.org/maven2/com/diffplug/spotless/spotless-maven-plugin/2.43.0/spotless-maven-plugin-2.43.0.module'\nprint(urllib.request.urlopen(url, timeout=10).read().decode()[:8000])\nPY", "timeout": 15}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2626, "output": 475, "cacheRead": 49664, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 52765, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1781030919605, "responseId": "resp_0ab6c4ff17837145016a2860086bb88190b548c8eb7cca728c"}}
