[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Implementing API Methods**\n\nI'm considering how to implement methods while avoiding deprecated APIs. It's important because we might have to deal with an interface that uses deprecated interface methods. I wonder if using a DefaultResourceManager with private constructor for injection would work. While I could consider mocks, they might not fit well. It's interesting that we might avoid using FileLocator for FormatterFactory but need it for FormatterStep.\n\nCreating FormatterConfig with nulls for testing could be a way forward, using MavenProject with real files. I'd like to implement a minimal ResourceManager too!\n\n**Exploring Dependencies**\n\nI'm looking into whether I need to add plexus-resources to the public API. It seems like they should be available transitively. I should test importing PlexusResource and see what exceptions come up. \n\nIn Gradle, it’s interesting how runtime dependencies for testImplementation might behave differently from compile dependencies. Also, it appears tests can't import FileLocator, which is in the plugin. I wonder if the ResourceManager class will require plexus-resources on the compile classpath due to plugin metadata. Checking module metadata will help clarify things!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0ab6c4ff17837145016a28600945bc819098e456b47a0d66f6\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqKGAWjceh-W6uOK8AmzuYmK99YHiORSdakwzzZg0c2d830ae3Y3Jc-8CkDyCjQOHFZyUxlgqi5WSwNvQKnPBxuLBnrU61_2_B8yMZrmMtHadfgqL12FWIgKzd_kWF6Dk6sQc4M74RzWqnFTAOME6QrWPv1jpcJ4yvXTRNBpm2_0Q2UJI39VXS0cFWxb8r5EV2Wi4d6MIDkt9wwSjK4GeJxZZrMrOh4i2DZYB7MLdo_VB20H1biWfnyREC6ocT2P-Ouru-igvcrbsVGI2-QzppvmSzQO1rAJadV7qKsPbDSbjarFb_GI36xWAdRqf3LSiO1rqfi4voMBM8iyIKT9PFJ6i-Rd6VmPStlBO6AXe3S4vM1ZLUe7M1c_SLxvr9eNF5WGqVBweOUrql45bQJVRNsZRAe-yf8dFaVUE_yV99pSqYQ6yRCtW6UZj1f98NK-iIT4vzE_E0CWwpcQuwrKVsWhUhqcp05T9d7ROnHdbbYuZYa6Orlz7